  "market_context": "Light Crude Oil Futures on February 8, 2024. Price was in a bullish context. During the London session (02:00–05:00 EST), price made a move lower into the previous range, forming a series of down-close candles before reversing, signaling a Change in State of Delivery to the upside.",
  "key_observation": "During London (02:00–05:00), price dipped into the prior range and printed a series of down-close candles, then closed above them — confirming a London Reversal and Change in State of Delivery. This set up a bullish New York continuation trade using the down-close candle sequence as an order block entry.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the 15-minute chart, the analyst observed that during the London session (02:00–05:00 EST) price made a move lower, reaching into the previous range and forming a series of down-close candles.",
    "Step 2: The analyst identified that price then closed above the series of down-close candles, confirming a Change in State of Delivery (CHoCH) and classifying the session as a London Reversal profile.",
    "Step 3: The analyst noted that with a bullish London Reversal confirmed, the expectation for New York was a continuation higher — consistent with the Power of Three (Accumulation, Manipulation, Distribution) framework.",
    "Step 4: The analyst dropped to the 5-minute chart as New York approached (08:30 EST) and observed price in a consolidation range, identifying the series of down-close candles as an order block for entry.",
    "Step 5: The analyst planned a long entry at the order block formed by the down-close candle sequence, placing a stop-loss below the swing low of that structure.",
    "Step 6: After entry, the analyst observed that the order block was retested and held, with the prior order block now acting as a propulsion block, confirming stacked institutional interest.",
    "Step 7: The analyst targeted 2R as the take-profit, which was reached, and then zoomed back out to the 15-minute chart to confirm that London had formed the wick of the daily candle while New York delivered the continuation — completing an Open-Low-High-Close daily candle structure."
  ],
  "outcome": "Long trade triggered at the 08:30 order block on the 5-minute chart. The propulsion block was retested and held. Price reached the 2R target. The daily candle completed as an Open-Low-High-Close, confirming the London Reversal profile.",
  "lessons": "When London (02:00–05:00) sweeps a low and closes back above a series of down-close candles, it signals a Change in State of Delivery. New York then provides the continuation entry via the order/propulsion block formed at that reversal, targeting at minimum 2R and completing the daily candle's Open-Low-High-Close structure.",
